WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.680
Hi everyone, I'm Mina Chetinkaya Randall and I'm here to tell you a bit about rstudio

00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:19.559
conf 2019 and specifically the Train-the-Trainer Workshop I'll be giving ahead of the conference.

00:00:19.559 --> 00:00:23.400
This is a two-day workshop and on the first day I will be joined by my colleague Gerrit

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:27.760
Grollemund to teach you how to teach short R courses and workshops.

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:31.440
On the second day you'll have the choice of choosing between the two tracks, how to

00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:35.599
teach Shiny, which will be taught by me, and how to teach the tidyverse, which will be

00:00:35.599 --> 00:00:37.599
taught by Gerrit.

00:00:37.599 --> 00:00:41.860
This workshop is a rare opportunity for those of you who are considering branching out from

00:00:41.860 --> 00:00:47.520
using R to also teaching R, as well as those who already might specialize in teaching R

00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:48.919
but would like to improve.

00:00:48.919 --> 00:00:54.560
I'm calling this a rare opportunity as many trainers and educators often go from being

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:59.560
practitioners to teachers without training in between about how to teach.

00:00:59.560 --> 00:01:03.080
This was certainly true for me at the beginning of my teaching career.

00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:08.000
However, I've found workshops, books, and other resources on how to teach more effectively

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:11.120
to be incredibly helpful for improving my own teaching.

00:01:11.120 --> 00:01:14.879
Therefore, I'm very excited to share what I know about teaching R and Shiny with all

00:01:14.879 --> 00:01:15.879
of you.

00:01:15.879 --> 00:01:20.480
I'm also super excited about the opportunity to spend two days working with teachers of

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:21.480
R.

00:01:21.879 --> 00:01:26.000
So, what did you expect from the Train the Trainer workshop?

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:30.800
On day one of our workshop, we will discuss best practices, pedagogical choices, and tips

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:34.680
for creating effective examples and activities.

00:01:34.680 --> 00:01:39.080
More specifically, we will present practical activities that you can use immediately to

00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:43.959
improve your presentation style, learning outcomes, and student engagement.

00:01:43.959 --> 00:01:48.580
The goal is for you to leave the class with a cognitive model of learning that you can

00:01:48.580 --> 00:01:53.180
use to develop your own effective workshops or courses within your organization.

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:59.260
Additionally, we will cover how to use RStudio Cloud and its curriculum of tutorials to jumpstart

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:01.279
your own lessons.

00:02:01.279 --> 00:02:04.220
On day two, we will ask you to make a tough choice.

00:02:04.220 --> 00:02:08.580
Do you want to learn more about teaching Shiny or teaching the tidyverse?

00:02:08.580 --> 00:02:13.460
Those who pick Shiny will join me for a full day of training on teaching Shiny at the beginner

00:02:13.460 --> 00:02:15.300
and intermediate levels.

00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:19.619
Over the past, I have developed and taught a variety of Shiny courses and workshops,

00:02:19.619 --> 00:02:21.699
both in person and online.

00:02:21.699 --> 00:02:26.259
We will build on materials from these courses and workshops, as well as from the upcoming

00:02:26.259 --> 00:02:31.720
book on Shiny by Joe Cheng, the creator of the Shiny package, and share examples that

00:02:31.720 --> 00:02:37.460
cover the entire lifecycle of a Shiny app, that is, build, improve, and share.

00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:42.220
A huge bonus of the workshop is that you will receive the course materials for teaching

00:02:42.220 --> 00:02:46.300
Mastering Shiny, RStudio's two-day Shiny workshop.

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:51.860
Additionally, participants will receive the RStudio Certified Shiny Instructor Certificate.

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:55.699
This workshop is for you if you're a training partner or want to become one, or if you're

00:02:55.699 --> 00:03:00.779
interested in the certification, or if you're an advocate for R in your organization.

00:03:00.779 --> 00:03:05.419
We expect participants to be proficient with Shiny coming into the workshop.

00:03:05.419 --> 00:03:09.820
Please visit the conference website to learn more about my and others' workshops, and I'm

00:03:09.820 --> 00:03:12.619
very much looking forward to seeing you all in Austin.

